GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_actual_token_here # Github token permitting Argos to access PRs.
ARGOS_DIRECTIVES_PATH=/Users/john/projects/argos-monorepo/.argos/directives # The path to the directives (rules) you want Argos to reference when reviewing PRs.
TARGET_GITHUB_REPO=jadenmounteer/argos-1 # The repo Argos-1 will look at when reviewing PRs.

# Generate the Github token:

# Log in to your GitHub account.

# Click your profile photo (top right) → Settings.

# Scroll down the left sidebar to Developer settings.

# Click Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic).

# Click Generate new token → Generate new token (classic).

# Note: Give it a name like ARGOS_DEMO_2026.

# Expiration: Set it to 7 or 30 days (keep it short for security).

# Select Scopes:

# repo (Full control of private repositories) — Needed to read the code.

# read:org (Read org data) — Needed if using a GitHub Org.
